<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm252492304">
<term>capitalization</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm234194112">process in which a long-term asset is recorded on the balance sheet and its allocated costs are expensed on the income statement over the asset’s economic life</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm236946928">
<term>current expense</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm249333984">cost to the business that is charged in the current period</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm262494528">
<term>depreciation</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm248054208">process of allocating the costs of a tangible asset over the asset’s economic life</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm257454800">
<term>investment</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm260716416">short-term and long-term asset that is not used in the day-to-day operations of the business</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
